<subSubSection pageNumber="750" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="750">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Note: 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Penaeaceae" genus="Plectronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Plectronia Linnaeus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">nom. rej</emphasis>
. in favour of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Penaeaceae" genus="Olinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Olinia</emphasis>
Thunb.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="750" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageNumber="750">
The name was evidently based on a mixture including 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Lam." authorityName="Lam." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Canthium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inerme">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Canthium inerme</emphasis>
(L.) Lam.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rubiaceae</taxonomicName>
) (as to the fruit characters and the Burman synonym). The rest of the generic description (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Mant. Pl</emphasis>
.: 6) was drawn from specimens in LINN, as noted by Bullock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Kew Bull</emphasis>
. 1932: 354. 1932). Sheet 277.2 (LINN) is accepted as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, with 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Cufod." authorityName="Cufod." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Penaeaceae" genus="Olinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ventosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">Olinia ventosa</emphasis>
(L.) Cufod.
</taxonomicName>
as the correct name for the taxon, as treated by Sebola &amp; Balkwill (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="750">S. African J. Bot</emphasis>
. 65: 100. 1999).
</paragraph>
